<HEAD>Singer May Buy Hotel</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Retransmits to fix cycle designator</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kenny Rogers says he is negotiating with
Lloyd's International Inc. to buy the $69 million Stouffer
Nashville Hotel.
   ``I would like to get into the hotel management business,''
Rogers said Friday in an address before some 1,000 radio station
managers attending a seminar. ``I'd like to own more than one.''
   The hotel, which opened last August, adjoins the new Nashville
Convention Center.
   Lloyd's has said the 673-room hotel is for sale. In January
1987, the international financial giant took over the interest
formerly held by a limited partnership. Prior to that, it was the
lead financing institution on bonds issued to finance the hotel.
   Rogers is known for hits such as ``The Gambler'' and ``Islands
in the Stream,'' a duet with Dolly Parton.
